- [ ] All array operations in UI code guard against null/undefined and use data ?? [] or Array.isArray guards
- [ ] All useState initializations for array data are typed as useState<Type[]>([]) and not useState(null)
- [ ] API integrations handle response shapes safely: data validation and fallbacks to [] where appropriate
- [ ] Security constraints validated: RBAC gating, protected routes, and sensitive actions logged
- [ ] UI interactions have accessible focus states and keyboard operability; visual design adheres to the provided theme

## UI/UX Guidelines
Apply the project’s design system and the following visual style:
- Use the provided color palette for primary actions, accents, and surfaces
- Serif display typography for headings to achieve premium editorial feel
- Sans-serif body typography for readability
- Cards with 16–20px radii, soft shadows, hover lift interactions
- Navigation: white header bar with centered links and right-aligned controls
- Data visualization should be neutral with teal/green accents if added
- Interactive elements: rounded primary green buttons, secondary actions in teal/gray-teal

## Visual Style

### Color Palette:
- Primary Green: #2f6f63
- Secondary Teal/Gray-Teal: #2b6250
- Neutral White: #ffffff
- Page Background Taupe: #a79e96
- Hero Beige: #f3efe6
- Text Dark: #1f1f1f
- Body Text Gray: #555555
- Card Shadow: rgba(0,0,0,0.08)
- Accent Brown: #3b2b1e
- Accent Orange CTA: #e07a4c

### Typography & Layout:
- Heading Typography: serif display font (e.g., Playfair Display or Georgia)
- Body Typography: sans-serif (e.g., Inter or Roboto)
- Hierarchy: hero heading > subheading > body text
- Layout: wide hero with centered content, generous padding, 12-column implied grid; max content width 900–1000px for hero
- Spacing: 24–32px gaps between sections; ample vertical rhythm

### Key Design Elements
- Card Design: white cards, 16–20px radii, soft shadows
- Navigation: white top bar with logo left, links center, actions right
- Data Visualization: neutral with teal/green accents
- Interactive Elements: rounded green primary buttons; forms with light borders and teal/green focus rings

### Design Philosophy
- Professional fintech aesthetic; data-forward visuals; premium typography; accessible and depth through shadows and rounded corners

## Mandatory Coding Standards — Runtime Safety (recap)
- Null-safety: data ?? [] for arrays
- Guard array calls: (items ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : []
- useState with arrays: useState<Type[]>([])
- API shapes: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
- Optional chaining: obj?.property?.nested
- Destructuring defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}

